---
import Base from '@brandon_m_behring/book-scaffold-astro/layouts/Base.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

const chapters = await getCollection('chapters', (entry) => !entry.data.draft);
chapters.sort((a, b) => (a.data.chapter ?? 0) - (b.data.chapter ?? 0));
---
<Base title="Agentic Systems Design: Environment & Context Engineering" description="A standalone volume on engineering the two layers around the model — the environment an agent acts in, and the context it reasons over. Authored from strict-live research.">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Agentic Systems Design</h1>
    <p class="subtitle"><em>Environment &amp; Context Engineering</em></p>

    <p>This volume is about the discipline that turns a model into an agent: engineering the <strong>environment</strong> it acts in and the <strong>context</strong> it reasons over. It is self-contained — it assumes a capable model and a harness, and develops the two layers around them.</p>

    <h2>Scope</h2>
    <p><strong>Covered here:</strong> the environment (repo &amp; doc design, the instruction layer, skills, guardrails, working at scale) and the context (why windows degrade, how to assemble them, how to persist them across sessions).</p>
    <p><strong>Adjacent — planned companion volumes, not yet available:</strong> Orchestration &amp; Multi-Agent (build-vs-buy, sub-agents), Tools &amp; MCP, Evaluation &amp; Operations, and Prompting. This book points outward to them where its scope ends; it does not depend on them.</p>

    <h2>Chapters</h2>
    <ul>
      {chapters.map((c) => (
        <li>
          <a href={`/chapters/${c.id}/`}>
            {c.data.chapter ? `Chapter ${c.data.chapter}: ` : ''}{c.data.title}
          </a>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>

    <h2>Other pages</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/chapters/">Chapter listing</a> (auto-generated)</li>
      <li><a href="/search/">Search</a> (Pagefind)</li>
      <li><a href="/references/">References</a></li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</Base>
